cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the recognition of handwritten characters using neural classifiers and feature extraction techniques. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper also involves the use of information retrieval techniques such as weighted majority voting, which could potentially place it under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
